The China Children's Center will host a series of activities to let children experience "high-tech" during "June 1st" - Xinhua News.
Xinhua News, Beijing, May 20th (Reported by Huang Xiaoxi and Zhou Shanshan) - Reporters learned from the China Children's Center on the 20th that from May 28th to June 1st, during and after the Children's Day "June 1st", the China Children's Center plans to host a series of activities such as children's maker experience, children's visual arts festival, and parent-child literary carnival, to let children experience the charm of cutting-edge technology during "June 1st".
It is understood that the activities hosted by the China Children's Center during this year's "June 1st" Children's Day include the "Love Home Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival, the first Children's Visual Arts Festival, the "Literary Carnival", and the "Family Love Reading" picture book series activities.
Li Zhongming, the Vice Director of China Children's Center, introduced at the 2016 "June 1st" Children's Day media conference held on the 20th, that the "Love Home Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival is the key activity for celebrating "June 1st" this year at the China Children's Center.
The activity focuses on combining social innovation with personal and family creativity, and allowing children and families to participate in various innovative education activities to make innovation a cultural gene in everyday families and to make "hands-on doing" a new way of learning and living for families.
It is reported that the "Love Home Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival includes dozens of cutting-edge technology experience content such as "Bean Fruit Maker" experience activities, the anniversary of the Old Cow Children's Exploration Museum and the "Exploring the Love of the Whole Family for Children's Meng Over Six One" activity, VR all-people experience plan, "Maker Tribe" interactive workshop, and more.